<div id="review_3398412158" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3398412158" />
    <a title="Susy  *MotherLambReads*" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/47238252-susy-motherlambreads"><img alt="Susy  *MotherLambReads*" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1539980236p2/47238252.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3398412158?book_show_action=true">Mar 05, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Susy  *MotherLambReads*" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Susy  *MotherLambReads*" href="/user/show/47238252-susy-motherlambreads">Susy  *MotherLambReads*</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/47238252-susy-motherlambreads?shelf=read-aloud-to-kids">read-aloud-to-kids</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3398412158" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18117127062753151435">“Baby, we have no choice of what color we&apos;re born or who our parents are or whether we&apos;re rich or poor. What we do have is some choice over what we make of our lives once we&apos;re here.”<br/><br/>I give it a 5!<br/>Littles gave it a 4. I asked them why... they said because they didn&apos;t like how the story ended with TJ!<br/><br/>&quot;What had happened to T.J. in the night I did not understand, but I knew that it would not pass. And I cried for those things which had happened in the night and would not pass.”<br/><br/>This book has given m</span>
  <span id="freeText18117127062753151435" style="display:none">“Baby, we have no choice of what color we're born or who our parents are or whether we're rich or poor. What we do have is some choice over what we make of our lives once we're here.”<br /><br />I give it a 5!<br />Littles gave it a 4. I asked them why... they said because they didn't like how the story ended with TJ!<br /><br />"What had happened to T.J. in the night I did not understand, but I knew that it would not pass. And I cried for those things which had happened in the night and would not pass.”<br /><br />This book has given me so so many opportunities to talk with them about race, racism, differences, hate, love, modern day racism, and so much more. Not only did it give me a chance to say not all stories end how we want them too- it gave us a chance to be in someone else's shoes and experience (to a much lesser degree) what the pain and hatred they did. That is empathy! That is why we read and learn!<br /><br />At the end of the book we heard the author say WHY this book and it's story needs to be out there. WHY these stories and words matter. I agree with her whole heartedly and will press this book into everyone's hands. At certain times, I would pause the audio or stop where I was reading and explain why the "N" word is used and what it means and meant in this historical time period. <br /><br />“Roll of thunder hear my cry Over the water bye and bye Ole man comin’ down the line Whip in hand to beat me down But I ain’t gonna let him Turn me ’round”</span>
  <a data-text-id="18117127062753151435" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
